  "body": "Hey guys. Trying to migrate from Truffle to hardhat but got an issue: \r\nI'm running the hyperledger-fabric evm. When trying to deploy the contract to the network I recieve this kind of error: \r\n`ProviderError: rpc: can't find service \"web3.ClientVersion`\r\nSeems like hh is trying to query the rpc with this:\r\n` {\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"web3_clientVersion\",\"id\":1}`\r\nAnd rpc response is \r\n`rpc: can't find service \"web3.ClientVersion\"`\r\n\r\nHow this could be resolved? \r\n\r\nps\r\nIn truffle you just set the network type to \r\n`type: \"fabric-evm\"`",
